		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=6345"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
 
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=6345')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&amp;TOPIC_ID=4652&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Tapping+advice+I+once+received%2E%2E%2E"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> This may be more for the younger types, but I wanted to pass it along...</P><P>I was once told by a high level necro to never tap at full health, to instead hold off, and cast something more mana effcienct until either lich or combat or reverse tifetap or whatever hurt me.</P><P>Why? Because to a necro hp = mana because of our liches, and its a waste of free mana to tap at full health.</P><P>** A tap is like a dd that kicks back hp, unless you are full hp </P><P>But to us, hp IS mana, with lich, so substituting mana for hp, we get:</P><P>** A tap is like a dd that kicks back mana, unless you are full hp.</P><P>So a tap is even LESS efficient to cast when you are full health.</P><P>---</P><P>HIGH END EXAMPLE: TOUCH OF NIGHT AND ARCH LICH</P><P>Scenario One - Full health</P><P>Touch of Night<BR>720 damage<BR>405 mana<BR>0 hp kicked back due to being full health, so no hp give to the lich machine<BR>405 cost</P><P>1.78 damage per mana</P><P>-</P><P>Scenario Two - Down 720 or more hp</P><P>Touch of Night<BR>720 tap<BR>405 mana<BR>720 hp kicked back due to being "hurt"<BR>475 mana back over time due to .660 ratio of arch lich hp -&gt; mana<BR>-70 cost, when all hp kicked is converted back to mana</P><P>inifinitely effcient (720 / -70) you actually get mana back</P><P>---</P><P>LOW LEVEL EXAMPLE: SIPHON LIFE AND ALLURE OF DEATH </P><P>Scenario One - Full Health</P><P>Siphon Life<BR>75 damage<BR>72 mana<BR>0 hp kicked back due to being full health, so no hp give to the lich machine<BR>72 cost</P><P>1.04 damage per mana</P><P>-</P><P>Scenario Two - Down 75 or more hp</P><P>Siphon Life<BR>75 damage<BR>72 mana<BR>75 hp kicked back due to being "hurt"<BR>37 mana back over time due to .5 ratio of allure of death hp -&gt; mana<BR>35 cost, when all hp kicked is converted back to mana</P><P>2.14 damage per mana (twice as efficient)</P><P>---</P><P>So, if you are at full health and want to do some damage, find another way, and wait till you are damaged to cast your taps, and you should be more efficient.</P><P>Thanks.</P><P></P><P></P><P></P><P></P><P></P><P></P><P>Noct<BR>10th Necromancer of Paineel</font></td>

