        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=36689&amp;TOPIC_ID=4652&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Tapping+advice+I+once+received%2E%2E%2E&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Thought I'd add an exception to this.  A lot of mobs are going to resist everything but your tap.  In this case, your tap nuke is your only option.  However, sacrifice a spell slot and throw in a "pact" spell.  As soon as your puller arrives with a mob, start pacting him.  Then tap to replace that life.</P><P>In Velks last night, our cleric went AFK for a while and I played healer.  I'd throw a pact as soon as the puller got back, then tap once to replace the life I lost, then Bond of death, pact him again (when first wears off).  Then pact him one more time when that one wears off. I was staying near full life, doing about 1000 damage to mob (plus pet) and healing the tank for about 1000 points per fight.  All the while staying between 85m and FM.</P><P>It only cost 10 mana to give someone else life so USE those pact spells.  Your group will love you for it.  You're sucking life anyways so you might as well give away your extra.  Just this one easy thing will take SOOO much pressure off of your healer.  Plus, it heals over time, so that last one is taking the tank back near full life while he's out pulling the next one.  Getting your timing down with this will make you a necro that people look for when starting groups.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
