         <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote><BR>I personally hate tapping when at full, or near full HP, it really does seem like a waste - so, what do I do?</P><P>I bust out my trusty Sacrificial Dagger and go poke whatever im fighting for a couple damage taking a few hits (around 100 dmg) then I back off, fear/let pet tank again and tap that HP back.</P><P>[size=1]<b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=54401" target="_blank">Azumaan</a></b><br>33 Erudite Necromancer<BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>Actually at 33, you are the perfect level to be swinging a Staff of Writhing.  Thing is 1HB, procs a 48(?) point DD a few times per fight and as you say, if you get hit a few times you can always tap it back.  If that stick procs three times in a fight and you do another 50 points of whack damage, that is 200 points of damage for zero mana.  Melee damage is amazingly mana efficient, and is very helpful until you hit 44 (when the pet is actually bad enough to be tanking mobs, and the mobs hit too hard for a level 44 necro to be tanking (re: spectres and giants))</P><P>Glonoin</P><P>Using your dead bodies to create a better tomorrow..<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
